Introduces a comprehensive API testing script that automates the testing of various forms on the IAC website.
The script includes functionality for generating test data, validating API responses, and logging results for different endpoints such as registration, contact, application, feedback, school requests, and parent/student requests.

Adds testing setup script for IAC Website
Implements a comprehensive setup script to streamline the testing environment for the IAC Website.
The script checks for Node.js installation, installs necessary testing dependencies, sets up Playwright browsers, creates a local environment file, updates the .gitignore for coverage directories, and verifies test scripts in package.json.
Additionally, it includes a smoke test to confirm the setup functionality, enhancing overall testing efficiency and usability.

Configures Playwright for parallel testing across major browsers, including mobile viewports, and integrates a web server setup for local development.
Enhances testing framework for better reliability and workflow efficiency.
